author: JENNIFER KOPF | Staff Writer
title: 551 West chef makes it to next round of Hometown Breakfast Battle
text:
Comments THOMAS' ENGLISH MUFFINS 
The All in One Muffin, the contest entry of chef Andrew James of Lancaster's 551 West, includes eggs, cheese, sausage, bacon, peanut butter -- and Thomas' English Muffins. 
From 135 chefs, 16 still are standing â€” and one of them is Andrew "Drew" James of 551 West in Lancaster city. 
The Hometown Breakfast Battle, sponsored by Thomas' English Muffins, has winnowed out its roster of contestants from the first round, and James has made the cut. 
His creation, an All in One Muffin, garnered enough votes to make it into the second round. It's a protein-lover's delight, with healthy fats and whole grains rounding out the ingredients. (Curious and hungry for the recipe? You can find it here ). 
The next round of voting has begun, and will cut the 16 remaining contestants down to eight. To vote, visit the Hometown Breakfast Battle website, then create a user name and password or sign in through social media. Voting in this round concludes Oct. 5. Tags
